'''Star Comics''' was an imprint of [[Marvel Comics]] which started in [[1984]] and continued to publish comic books into the mid-1990s. Titles published by the imprint were aimed at younger readers and were often adaptations of children's television animated series. Titles published by the imprint included ''Peter Porker, The Spectacular Spider-Ham''; ''ThunderCats''; and ''The Get-Along Gang''. Star also briefly published a comic which starred the comedian John Candy, an adaptation of his cartoon show ''Camp Candy''.

Star Comics printed two short-lived ''[[Star Wars]]'' spin-off series, [[Star Wars: Droids (1986)|''Droids'']] and [[Ewoks (Marvel)|''Ewoks'']]. Both were based on the animated series of the same name. Furthermore, one issue of [[The Muppet Show|''Muppet Babies'']] was a ''Star Wars'' parody. The digest-sized ''[[Star Comics Magazine]]'' reprinted stories from multiple series, several including stories from ''Ewoks''.

